Senator Ike Ekweremadu, and his wife, Beatrice Nwanneka Ekweremadu, have been arrested by the United Kingdom for organ harvesting. The metropolitan police who confirmed the arrest on Thursday said the duo was charged with conspiring to bring a child to the UK in order to harvest organs. The arrest followed an investigation by the force’s specialist crime team. The Police said that they have been remanded in custody and will appear at Uxbridge Magistrates’ Court today. “A child has been safeguarded and we are working closely with partners on continued support. “As criminal proceedings are now underway we will not be providing further details.”